
						Unit tests for MAK program

Uses FRUIT and FRUITpy for unit tests

If python is not avialable, pure fortran will be used

For more info about FRUIT and FRUITpy, read:
	https://sourceforge.net/projects/fortranxunit/
	https://github.com/mortele/FRUIT
	https://github.com/acroucher/FRUITPy


					MAK/unit_tests/
						|
						|
		-----------------------------------------------------------------
		|		|		|		|		|	
	     fruit/	  fruit_drivers/      vers/	    makefile 	      README	
		|               |
	        |    		|------------------------
                |               |   	   |            |
	 test_module.f90     fruit.py   makefile  fruit_driver.f90


fruit/
	Contains unit-test routines for module routines from MAK/src/<module>.f90
	If <module>.f90 is tested, the name of the file in MAK/unit_tests/fruit/ should be test_<module>.f90

fruit_drivers/
	Contains following files: fruit.f90 fruit.py fruit_driver.f90 and Makefile
	fruit.f90 		- FRUIT source code
	fruit.py  		- python script to run FRUITpy interface
	Makefile 		- Makefile to compile unit tests. Usually called by fruit.py
	fruit_driver.f90	- driver to run unit-tests. This is manual version used if FRUITpy is not avilable. 
				  Usually created by fruit.py

vers/
	Compiled version of unit-tests

makefile
	makefile to run unit tests.
	Usage:
		make vers		(vers = std / cmx)

README
	Documentation about unit-tests.
